'''Nakayama Shrine''' (????????) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|WD=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Minokamo|Q857305|WD=Q857305|1=Minokamo, Gifu}}.

It is a candidate shrine for Nakayama Shrine of the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmy?ch?|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} in {{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|WD=Q864156|1=Mino Province}}{{ill|lt=Kamo District|Q1348656|WD=Q1348656|lt=Kamo District|1=Kamo District, Gifu}} (the other candidate shrine is {{ill|lt=Suwa Shrine (Minokamo)|Q11631934|WD=Q11631934|lt=Suwa Shrine|1=Suwa Shrine (Q11631934)}}).

=== History ===
Its founding date is unknown. It was destroyed by fire in wartime during the {{ill|lt=Eiroku|Q1143341|WD=Q1143341|1=Eiroku}} era, and no records remain from before that.

It was rebuilt in Eiroku 12 ({{ill|lt=1569|Q6653|WD=Q6653|1=1569}}). After that, records of shrine construction and rebuilding exist for the {{ill|lt=Keich?|Q1328185|WD=Q1328185|1=Keichō}}, {{ill|lt=Kan'ei|Q1192913|WD=Q1192913|1=Kan'ei}}, and {{ill|lt=Enp?|Q1145735|WD=Q1145735|1=Enpō}} eras.

It is said that {{ill|lt=Suwa Shrine (Minokamo)|Q11631934|WD=Q11631934|lt=Suwa Shrine|1=Suwa Shrine (Q11631934)}} moved and rebuilt Nakayama Shrine by order of {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kota Genryu|1=UNKNOWN}}, lord of {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Yoneda Castle|1=UNKNOWN}}, then enshrined {{ill|lt=Suwa Taisha|Q218813|WD=Q218813|1=Suwa-taisha}} of {{ill|lt=Shinano Province|Q289250|WD=Q289250|1=Shinano Province}} and renamed it Suwa Shrine. The current Nakayama Shrine is thought to be a shrine rebuilt at the original location.

=== Enshrined deity ===
*{{ill|lt=Kanayamahiko|Q4387856|WD=Q4387856|lt=Kanayamahiko-no-Mikoto|1=Kanayama-hiko and Kanayama-hime}}
*:There is also a theory identifying this deity as {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata-no-Kami|1=Takeminakata}}

